HEADWORD: Neigh
<hw>Neigh</hw> <pr>(n⟦amac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Neighed</conjf> <pr>(n⟦amac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Neighing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>neien</ets>, AS. <ets>hn⟦aemac⟧gan</ets>, prob. of imitative
origin; cf. MHG. <ets>n⟦emac⟧gen</ets>, Icel. <ets>hneggja</ets>,
<ets>gneggja</ets>, Sw. <ets>gn⟦aum⟧gga</ets>. Cf. <er>Nag</er> a
horse.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To utter the cry of the horse; to
